  "doc_id": "18201",
  "text": "Bilotta et al. [CITATION_1] described an elegant construction for MU codes based on well-known combinatorial objects termed Dyck sequences. A Dyck sequence of length 2n is a binary sequence composed of n zeros and n ones such that no prefix of the sequence has more zeros than ones. By definition, a Dyck sequence is balanced and it necessarily starts with a one and ends with a zero. The number of Dyck word of length 2n is the n-th Catalan number, equal to 1 n+1 2n n .",
